CloudExchange colocation allows organizations to connect to Azure through a third-party exchange provider.

This model uses shared infrastructure for connectivity.

For example, companies colocate their servers in a facility that connects directly to Azure.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is enterprises using Equinix data centers for connectivity.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is reducing latency by connecting through nearby exchange points.

This model provides efficient and scalable connectivity options.
